  "texts": [
    "The DSLs transform the problem from the human readable form to a lower level form (often a cone program) suitable for a solver.",
    "These DSLs make it easy to develop convex optimization based methods, as well as to modify, update, and maintain existing ones.",
    "As a result, CVXPY is used at many quantitative hedge funds today, as well as in many other applications and industries.",
    "The proposed extension of Markowitz's portfolio construction method that we describe below is a good example of the use of CVXPY.",
    "It is a complex problem involving nonlinear and nondifferentiable functions, but its specification in CVXPY takes only a few tens of lines of clear readable code, given in appendix B."
